	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Dar es Salaam - Flooding sparked by a hail and rainstorm killed 38 people in a village in north-western Tanzania on Wednesday, police said. More than 60 people were also injured in Mwakata. Widespread destruction of property was reported. Regional police commander Justus Kamugisha said rescuers were still searching for survivors or bodies. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  